        , 18: [ {class: "vs", text: "and said thus, O sirs, how exceedingly strong is wine! it causes all men to err that drink it:"} ]
        , 19: [ {class: "vs", text: "it makes the mind of the king and of the fatherless child to be all one; of the bondman and of the freeman, of the poor man and of the rich:"} ]
        , 20: [ {class: "vs", text: "it turns also every thought into cheer and mirth, so that a man remembers neither sorrow nor debt:"} ]
        , 21: [ {class: "vs", text: "and it makes every heart rich, so that a man remembers neither king nor local governor; and it makes to speak all things by talents:"} ]
        , 22: [ {class: "vs", text: "and when they are in their cups, they forget their love both to friends and kindred, and a little after draw their swords:"} ]
        , 23: [ {class: "vs", text: "but when they awake from their wine, they remember not what they have done."} ]
        , 24: [ {class: "vs", text: "O sirs, is not wine the strongest, seeing that it enforces to do thus? And when he had so spoken, he held his peace."} ]
